Once upon a time, in a small village near the sea, there lived a boy named Leo. Leo loved the sky very much. He had a special kind of rainbow that he called the "Sea Rainbow."

It was made of the colors of the ocean. When the sea waves hit the sky, they threw a rainbow of blue, green, and yellow. It looked like a big, shiny ball of water.

Leo walked to the edge of the beach every day. He watched the rainbows dance in the wind. Sometimes they were bright and colorful, like a party. Sometimes they were soft and faded, like a quiet evening.

One sunny morning, Leo sat on his garden bench. He felt very happy. He thought, "I can see the sea here." He smiled and said, "I love the Sea Rainbow."

The rain stopped, and the sea began to rise. The Sea Rainbow grew bigger and brighter. Leo felt like he was flying high above the water. He knew that no matter how big the rainbow got, it would always be beautiful.

Leo closed his eyes and listened to the waves. He knew that the Sea Rainbow was his favorite thing in the world. [end of text]


